# Change Policy

## 1. Purpose

Different governance phases permit different kinds of changes. This rule names them explicitly so the agent never silently expands authority.

Anchors:

- `.cursor/rules/00-siso.mdc` — request quality + CHAT/DISCOVERY/EXECUTION classification
- `.cursor/rules/70-execution-bridge.mdc` — the Scope Slice → User Story → code seam
- `.cursor/rules/feature-area-workflow.mdc` — the discovery hierarchy
- `.cursor/rules/execution-loop.mdc` — autonomous loop boundaries
- `.cursor/rules/79-pr-sizing.mdc` — per-PR scope limits

---

## 2. Mode → permitted changes

The agent classifies each request per `00-siso.mdc` (CHAT / DISCOVERY / EXECUTION). This rule defines **what changes each mode is allowed to make**.

### 2.1 CHAT

Conversation only. No file writes anywhere.

### 2.2 DISCOVERY

| Allowed writes | Path |
|---|---|
| PRD discovery capture | `docs/prd/notes/`, `docs/prd/questions/open-questions.md` (capture artifacts) |
| PRD persistence | `docs/prd/PRD.md`, `docs/prd/state.md`, `docs/prd/history.md`, `docs/prd/archive/` (only via `/prd update` after approval) |
| Product decisions | `docs/product-decisions/PD-NNN.md` (only after approval) |
| Feature Area files | `docs/product/feature-areas/<kebab>.md` (only via `/feature-area scaffold` / `promote` after approval) |
| Scope Slice files | `docs/product/scope-slices/<...>.md` (only via `/feature-area scaffold-slices` / `refine-slice` / `promote-slice` after approval) |
| Execution-loop tables | `docs/WORK_QUEUE.md`, `docs/BLOCKERS.md`, `docs/EXECUTION_LOG.md`, `docs/EXECUTION_LOCK.md`, `docs/POINTS_OF_ATTENTION.md` (only via `/execute-prd`) |
| `.cursor/` governance | only when the user explicitly requests rule / agent / skill / template / checker work |

Forbidden in DISCOVERY:

- Source code writes (`zedos/nextjs_space/src/**`, `app/**`, `lib/**`, `apps/**`, `packages/**`, `services/**`)
- Schema migrations (`prisma/**`, `packages/database/migrations/**`)
- Dependency installs (`package.json`, `pnpm-lock.yaml`)
- Build artifacts (`.next/`, `dist/`, `coverage/`, `*.tsbuildinfo`)

The `pre-edit` hook refuses these writes when the active SISO classification is DISCOVERY.

### 2.3 EXECUTION

EXECUTION mode is entered explicitly via one of these commands:

| Command | Permitted changes |
|---|---|
| `/explore` | Read-only — no writes |
| `/evol <description>` | Intake for product evolution (design fixes, UX improvements, feature enhancements). Small changes route to `/fix`; larger ones append a `candidate` row to `docs/WORK_QUEUE.md` + `docs/EXECUTION_LOG.md` (after `approved`) |
| `/bug <description>` | Intake for bug reports. Small non-critical bugs route to `/fix`; critical/data-integrity/security bugs append rows to `docs/BLOCKERS.md`, `docs/WORK_QUEUE.md`, `docs/POINTS_OF_ATTENTION.md` + `docs/EXECUTION_LOG.md` (after `approved`) |
| `/plan <slice-path>` | `docs/execution/plans/<...>.plan.md` (after explicit approval of the proposal) |
| `/implement <plan-path>` | Source code under the layout in effect (`zedos/nextjs_space/**` or `apps/**` + `packages/**`), within the Plan's `Touched Files` allow-list, after Patch Intent Summary `approved` |
| `/fix <issue>` | Same source-code authority as `/implement` but scoped to a smaller change |
| `/review` | Read-only — no writes |
| `/commit` | Stages and commits files already produced by `/implement` or `/fix` |
| `/pr` | Pushes the current branch and opens / updates a PR (no source-code edits at this step) |
| `/babysit` | Triages PR comments, resolves clear conflicts, fixes CI — small scoped fixes only |
| `/split` | Branch and PR creation only — no behavior changes; reorganizes existing diffs |
| `/improve-config` | `.cursor/**` only — improvements to the governance system itself |

EXECUTION never permits:

- Bypassing the Plan's `Touched Files` allow-list
- Writing to `docs/prd/**`, `docs/product/**`, or `docs/product-decisions/**` (DISCOVERY territory)
- Modifying `.cursor/rules/**` or `.cursor/checkers/**` outside `/improve-config`
- Adding dependencies via `/implement` without an explicit Plan section "Dependencies Added" listing each package + reason

---

## 3. Authority transitions (only via explicit command)

The agent does not switch modes silently. Mode transitions:

| From | To | Triggered by |
|---|---|---|
| CHAT | DISCOVERY | User runs a `/prd` or `/feature-area` mode |
| DISCOVERY | EXECUTION | User runs `/evol`, `/bug`, `/plan`, `/implement`, `/fix`, `/commit`, `/pr`, `/babysit`, `/split`, or `/improve-config` |
| EXECUTION | DISCOVERY | User runs a `/prd` or `/feature-area` mode (mid-implementation: agent stops, asks if discovery is intentional) |
| any | CHAT | User asks a question with no command |

Mid-implementation switches to DISCOVERY pause the active Plan — the Plan must be re-approved before execution resumes.

---

## 4. Implementation Plan as the authority document

In EXECUTION mode, the **approved Implementation Plan** is the single source of authority for "what code changes are allowed". Specifically, the Plan must declare:

| Plan section | Authority granted |
|---|---|
| `Touched Files (exact paths)` | The agent may edit only these paths |
| `Layers Affected` | The agent may cross only the listed layer boundaries |
| `Contracts Changed` | The agent may add/modify only the listed zod schemas |
| `Migrations` | The agent may add only the listed migration steps |
| `Dependencies Added` | The agent may install only the listed packages |
| `Tests` | The agent must add/update at least the listed test files |
| `Out of Scope` | The agent must not touch behavior listed here |

Anything outside the Plan's allow-lists requires a Plan revision (with new approval), not silent expansion.

---

## 5. Hard rules

1. **No silent mode escalation.** A request that arrives in DISCOVERY does not become EXECUTION because the agent thinks code would be useful — the user invokes the command.
2. **No source-code writes outside an approved Plan.** Hooks enforce this at the tool layer.
3. **No Plan execution without a Patch Intent Summary in the immediately preceding turn approved by the user.** `ok` is not approval.
4. **No dependency installs without explicit Plan declaration.**
5. **No `.cursor/` mutations outside `/improve-config`** except for the narrow scaffolding modes documented in `.cursor/commands/feature-area.md` and `.cursor/commands/prd.md`.
6. **No skipping the `/review` step** when the diff exceeds the small-change threshold (§2 of `79-pr-sizing.mdc`).

---

